          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 9045,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The recent update to the Consumer Rights Directive anchors financial services marketed at a distance into the horizontal framework, and, moreover, explicitly requires Member States to take measures limiting the use of dark pattern techniques. This addition ensures that the digital marketing and contracting of financial services already fall under specific EU-level restrictions against such practices.",
