          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 20340,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The introduction of new DFA rules that risk overlapping with existing sectoral or horizontal frameworks would risk legal uncertainty, complex compliance, and inconsistent approaches, as well as enforcement. Credit providers already face detailed requirements on advertising, pre-contractual information, fairness, and transparency under financial services and data protection laws.",
        "chunk_meta": {
